LRU Cache implementation, a Node class is required.Because:
    HashMap gives fast access to cache items
    Doubly Linked List maintains usage order
    Each element in the linked list must store:
          key
          value
          prev pointer
          next pointer

get(key):
exists ?
   yes → move to front
   no  → return -1

put(key, value)

already exists ?
   yes → remove old node

insert new node at front

capacity exceeded ?
   yes → remove tail.prev

remove(node)
  Suppose we remove B
  Before: head <-> A <-> B <-> C <-> tail
  Connections:
      B.prev = A
      B.next = C
Step 1
  Node prevNode = node.prev;  For B: prevNode = A
Step 2
    Node nextNode = node.next;
    nextNode = C
Step 3
    prevNode.next = nextNode;
    A.next = C 
    Now: A -----> C
Step 4
    nextNode.prev = prevNode;
    C.prev = A

Final: head <-> A <-> C <-> tail      

insert(node)
  We always insert near head because: newest/recently used item should become MRU
  Suppose current list: head <-> A <-> C <-> tail 
  Insert B 
    Goal: head <-> B <-> A <-> C <-> tail

Step 1
  Node nextNode = head.next;
  nextNode = A
Step 2
  head.next = node;
  head -> B
Temporary:
  head -> B
  A <-> C
Step 3
  node.prev = head;
  B.prev = head
Step 4
  node.next = nextNode;
  B.next = A
Step 5
  nextNode.prev = node;
  A.prev = B
Final:  head <-> B <-> A <-> C <-> tail

class LRUCache {
    
    static class Node{
        int key;
        int value;
        
        Node prev;
        Node next;
        
        Node(int key, int value){
            this.key = key;
            this.value = value;
        }
    }
        static int capacity;
        static HashMap<Integer, Node> map;
        
        static Node head;
        static Node tail;
    

    LRUCache(int cap) {
        // code here
        capacity =cap;
        map = new HashMap<>();
        head= new Node(0,0);
        tail= new Node(0,0);
        head.next=tail;
        tail.prev=head;
        
    }

    public static int get(int key) {

        
        //  code here
        if(!map.containsKey(key)){
            return -1;
        }
        
        Node node = map.get(key);
        remove(node);
        insert(node);
        
        return node.value;
    }

        
    public static void put(int key, int value) {
        //  code here
        
        if(map.containsKey(key)){
            Node oldNode = map.get(key);
            remove(oldNode);
            map.remove(key);
        }
        
        Node newNode= new Node(key,value);
        insert(newNode);
        map.put(key,newNode);
        
        if(map.size()> capacity){
            Node lru = tail.prev;
            remove(lru);
            map.remove(lru.key);
        }
    }
    
    static void remove(Node node){
        Node prevNode= node.prev;
        Node nextNode = node.next;
        
        prevNode.next= nextNode;
        nextNode.prev= prevNode;
        
    }
    
    static void insert(Node node){
        Node nextNode= head.next;
        
        head.next=node;
        node.prev=head;
        
        node.next=nextNode;
        nextNode.prev= node;
        
    }
}
